column43: Tangled in line, drug in backwards by tail.
Both tags were applied and then removed due to condition of shark; Spit hook at shore.
column48: Both tags were removed due to condition of shark.

column43: RBC's were pippeted and not washed with Ringer's Solution.
column48: PSAT washed up on Dewey's beach; Haven't heard from acoustic.

column43: Plasma was pink; Fishermen struggled to remove hook.
Fishermen struggled to remove hook; Caught on 80-wide reel.
column48: PSAT data suggests shark was eaten ~7 hrs post-release; Acoustic data confirms that notion.

column43: Sank after release with no swimming effort; Took a while to get shark situated at side of boat; Line cut and hook left in.
Fishermen struggled to remove hook; Shark rolled over in surf after release.
Caught on 50-wide reel; Bled badly post-hook removal.
column48: Shark was found on beach the morning after tagging it, with acoustic transmitter attached.
PSAT appears to be bitten off, was recovered on beach and returned.

column43: Shark washed back up after release and was released again.
Post-handling iSTAT wouldn't run; Plasma really red (and HCT)
